Ask HN: How to read algorithms and math notation in scientific papers?
text:
Hi! I'm a CS outsider, I write code but I'm not literated in computer science. I need to learn how to read both pseudo algorithms in papers and all the letter soup in math formulas, in the machine learning space. I had formal calculus and linear algebra in college, but that was 15 years ago.

Any tips are appreciated!

Thanks

What do you think – app to find other remote workers who like outdoor sports
text:
I've been working remotely for a while and whilst I met some awesome people on the way, keeping in touch with them and meeting new people in new places has become increasingly difficult. Probably because I'm less keen than in the past to hang out in hostels, go out drinking, etc. and would rather find friends for sports or active things to do, e.g., hikes, surf, paddle, climbing, cycling, etc. Daily beers and eating out hit differently after 30 :)

So, I'm building an app just for that - to find other nomads/ remote workers who share your sport interests, to keep in touch as you move spots and let your friends know when you're in a new location.

Thoughts?

I need feedback and testers and you can check it out here: https://bit.ly/3zpF4Kq

Cheers!
